This is a private AI system. Local inference only — no cloud AI APIs ever.

SERVICES:
- backend: FastAPI Python app, port 8000
- frontend: React/TypeScript Vite app, port 5173
- extension: Chrome Manifest V3 extension
- vscode-ext: VS Code extension in TypeScript

MODELS (all via Ollama at localhost:11434, three speed modes):
Balanced (default): deepseek-r1:14b (math), qwen2.5-coder:14b (code), qwen3:8b (chat), qwen2.5vl:7b (vision), nomic-embed-text (embed)
Fast: qwen2-math:7b-instruct (math), qwen2.5-coder:7b (code), qwen3:8b (chat), qwen2.5vl:7b (vision)
Deep: qwen2.5:32b (all roles except vision), qwen2.5vl:7b (vision)
Tab completion always uses qwen2.5-coder:7b regardless of speed mode.

ARCHITECTURE:
- Vector DB: ChromaDB at ./chroma_db
- Agent framework: LangGraph, nodes in backend/agents/
- Tools: backend/tools/ — python_exec, git, math (SymPy), web_search, file, test_runner
- Memory: ChromaDB (semantic) + knowledge graph (data/graph.json) + session state
- Speed mode: global server-side setting in backend/config/models.py, switchable via API

RULES:
- Always async/await in Python and TypeScript
- Always type-hint Python functions
- Always TypeScript strict mode
- Use pathlib.Path for all file paths (Windows compatible)
- When editing backend, check frontend/src/lib/api.ts for contract
- When adding agents, wire into backend/agents/graph.py
- Model strings are sacred — use exactly as listed above
- Speed mode is global — all clients share the same mode
- Deep mode requires VRAM unload of other models first
